1
00:00:01,542 --> 00:00:05,125
As time passes,
a boy inevitably becomes a man,

2
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:08,834
but what is<i> not</i> inevitable
is that a man become a warrior.

3
00:00:08,875 --> 00:00:11,834
A warrior must be forged,
like a sword,

4
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:15,250
tempered by...

5
00:00:15,291 --> 00:00:18,166
by...

6
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:21,458
tempered by experience.

7
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,000
The path of the warrior
begins with--

8
00:00:24,041 --> 00:00:25,542
(<i> giggling</i> )
Alexander?

9
00:00:25,583 --> 00:00:27,250
No! Wait!

10
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:29,583
(<i> child giggling</i> )

11
00:00:32,542 --> 00:00:33,917
Sorry.

12
00:00:33,959 --> 00:00:36,417
I didn't mean to hit<i> you.</i>

13
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,333
What is the meaning of this?

14
00:00:43,375 --> 00:00:44,709
I'm sorry.

15
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,667
We made fullerenes
in chemistry class today

16
00:00:46,709 --> 00:00:49,041
and filled them
with water.

17
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:51,291
I asked you to meet me here
after school.

18
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:52,875
I have been waiting
for you.

19
00:00:52,917 --> 00:00:54,834
I forgot.

20
00:00:54,875 --> 00:00:56,875
You forgot because
you allowed yourself

21
00:00:56,917 --> 00:00:58,709
to be distracted
by foolishness.

22
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:00,083
I'm sorry.

23
00:01:01,917 --> 00:01:03,750
(<i> sighs</i> )

24
00:01:03,792 --> 00:01:04,959
There is something
very important

25
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,125
I want to discuss
with you.

26
00:01:07,166 --> 00:01:08,583
It concerns
your future.

27
00:01:08,625 --> 00:01:10,667
Sit.

28
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:15,709
As time passes,

29
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:17,458
a boy inevitably
becomes a man,

30
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,000
but what is
not inevitable

31
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:20,875
is that a man
becomes a sword.

32
00:01:21,834 --> 00:01:23,083
What?

33
00:01:23,125 --> 00:01:26,333
No, I meant...
warrior.

34
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:28,000
The path of
a warrior begins

35
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:29,959
with the First
Rite of Ascension.

36
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,583
Is that when they hit you
with painstiks?

37
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:35,583
No. No, that is
the Second Rite.

38
00:01:35,625 --> 00:01:37,458
Oh.
You are approaching

39
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:38,959
the Age of Ascension.

40
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,750
It is time for you to
prepare for the ceremony.

41
00:01:41,792 --> 00:01:43,625
What do I have to do?

42
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:46,458
Well, your fighting
skills will be tested,

43
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:49,542
and your knowledge of
the teachings of Kahless.

44
00:01:49,583 --> 00:01:51,458
It will be
challenging,

45
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:54,834
but I will help you
prepare.

46
00:01:54,875 --> 00:01:58,000
These are the
<i>kor'tova</i> candles.

47
00:01:58,041 --> 00:01:59,917
They represent
the fire that burns

48
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:02,875
within the heart
of a warrior.

49
00:02:02,917 --> 00:02:04,166
When you light yours,

50
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:06,250
you<i> will</i> be declaring
your intention

51
00:02:06,291 --> 00:02:08,500
to become a warrior.

52
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,750
Go ahead.

53
00:02:11,792 --> 00:02:13,291
What if I don't
want to?

54
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,208
If you do not
participate in the rite

55
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:19,583
before the age of 13 years,
you will never be able

56
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:21,792
to become a true
Klingon warrior.

57
00:02:21,834 --> 00:02:24,208
Well, I don't care
about that.

58
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,667
You may not care
about it now,

59
00:02:25,709 --> 00:02:27,041
but someday you might.

60
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:28,333
Well, Mother always
said that--

61
00:02:28,375 --> 00:02:29,583
that I didn't have to
do any of

62
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,625
this Klingon stuff
if I didn't want to.

63
00:02:33,125 --> 00:02:34,792
It is your decision,
but--

64
00:02:34,834 --> 00:02:35,959
Okay, then.

65
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,291
I'm not going to
do it.

66
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,083
Alexander.

67
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:41,041
You just said
it was up to me.

68
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:43,250
I don't want to be
a warrior.

69
00:03:20,583 --> 00:03:24,959
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

70
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:29,166
<i>These are the voyages</i>
<i>of the starship Enterprise.</i>

71
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:30,792
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

72
00:03:30,834 --> 00:03:34,625
<i>to explore</i>
<i>strange new worlds,</i>

73
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:39,041
<i>to seek out new life</i>
<i>and new civilizations,</i>

74
00:03:39,083 --> 00:03:43,041
<i>to boldly go</i>
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

75
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:42,917
As a result, we won't
be able to rendezvous

76
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,000
with the<i> Kearsarge</i> 
for another four days.

77
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:47,083
Will we be holding position
here until it arrives?

78
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:49,291
Yes, and as
it would seem

79
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,166
that we're in for
a relatively quiet time,

80
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:52,542
I shall use
this opportunity

81
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:53,834
to visit
the Hatarian system.

82
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,875
There are some
ancient ruins

83
00:04:55,917 --> 00:04:57,709
that are just
being excavated.

84
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:59,500
The delay will also
make it possible

85
00:04:59,542 --> 00:05:01,250
for stellar dynamics
to complete their study

86
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:02,458
of the Vodrey Nebula.

87
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:03,792
I'll let them know
that they can have

88
00:05:03,834 --> 00:05:05,041
more access to the
lateral sensor grid.

89
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,458
We could use
this time

90
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:10,542
to recalibrate the weapons
targeting system.

91
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:13,959
Mr. Worf?

92
00:05:16,458 --> 00:05:17,667
Yes, um...

93
00:05:17,709 --> 00:05:19,875
I will begin
the procedure immediately.

94
00:05:21,417 --> 00:05:23,625
Very good.
Dismissed.

95
00:05:25,542 --> 00:05:27,500
Lieutenant?

96
00:05:27,542 --> 00:05:29,875
Could I have a word
with you for a moment?

97
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,208
I noticed several times
during the briefing

98
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:39,000
that you appeared
to be a bit distracted.

99
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:40,250
I apologize.

100
00:05:40,291 --> 00:05:41,542
In the future,
I will make sure

101
00:05:41,583 --> 00:05:42,792
my personal
affairs do not

102
00:05:42,834 --> 00:05:44,291
interfere with
my duties.

103
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:46,250
Is everything
all right?

104
00:05:48,417 --> 00:05:51,083
I'm having problems
with Alexander.

105
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:52,917
He has made it clear
he does not wish

106
00:05:52,959 --> 00:05:55,250
to participate in the
First Rite of Ascension.

107
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,417
Oh, I see.

108
00:05:57,458 --> 00:05:59,625
I tried to tell him
that it is

109
00:05:59,667 --> 00:06:01,458
an important part of
a young Klingon's life,

110
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,750
but... he does
not understand.

111
00:06:03,792 --> 00:06:05,125
But he's had
so little opportunity

112
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:07,917
to spend time
with Klingons.

113
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:12,583
You know, the Festival
of<i> Kot'baval</i> is tomorrow.

114
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:14,083
If he could
take part in that,

115
00:06:14,125 --> 00:06:17,000
I'm sure he would
more fully appreciate

116
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:20,458
what a rich cultural
heritage he comes from.

117
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,583
There<i> is</i> the Klingon
outpost on Maranga IV.

118
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:26,291
I'm sure they'll be
celebrating the festival.

119
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:28,208
Yes...

120
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,125
but the outpost is
on the other side

121
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:32,542
of the Vodrey Nebula.

122
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:34,250
It would take three days
by shuttle to get there.

123
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:35,750
Oh, the<i> Enterprise</i> 
could be there

124
00:06:35,792 --> 00:06:37,208
in a fraction of the time,
and still back

125
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,417
in time for
the rendezvous.

126
00:06:38,458 --> 00:06:39,667
Captain, I could
not ask you--

127
00:06:39,709 --> 00:06:41,250
Mr. Worf, stellar dynamics
would like

128
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:44,750
nothing better than
a trip around the nebula.

129
00:06:44,792 --> 00:06:46,709
Thank you, sir.

